author: National Geographic
description:
How do you help someone when the waves are crashing down around you? On what seemed like the perfect day, disaster struck in the form of a devastating tsunami. Swept apart from her husband, Rachel fought to stay alive. As the world around her shattered, only one question remained: would they ever find their way back to each other? 

Witness stories of hope, hardship, and heroism from the 2004 Indian Ocean Tsunami in Tsunami: Race Against Time, now streaming on Disney+ and Hulu.

author: National Geographic
description:
Join Antoni Porowski and chef Molly Wenk as they prepare a classic Polish comfort food: golumpki, also known as stuffed cabbage rolls. For our plant based friends, Antoni and Molly also teach us how to make golumpki vegetarian.

National Geographic's new series, No Taste Like Home with Antoni Porowski guides celebrity guests on epic journeys to explore their ancestral gastronomic roots.
